Do while loop in java

[Do while loop in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/do-while-loop-java/)

do while java executes the statements and then evaluates the expression/condition of loop’s body until given condition is true.

So do while loop is guaranteed to execute the body at least once. Here expression in do while loop should return a boolean value.

Here’s do while syntax java.

do{
   statement(s);
}while(expression/condition);

Here’s do while java program.

public class DoWhileLoopExample
{
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
      int a = 5;
      do {
          System.out.print(a);
          a++;
          System.out.print("\n");
      }while(a < 10);
   }
}


Output:

5
6
7
8
9
